I love New York Fries. They are well prepared fries and have plenty of options. There are lots of poutine options as it is the most popular type right now, but they also do various topped fries. They have the usual soft drinks but the fry dishes are the thing. Parking is available from the mall and they have access to the Canada Line station nearby for transit.
They do great and tasty fries but service isnt the best. The staff have no smiles, they just look grumpy as they handle your order.
Great corner location, away fr the madness of tje food court. The Works is my favourite. Usually quick service here.
If Im in the area, I will come here for poutine, they have a lot of options for fries. You can find anything fries here.
I dont even think I was there but whatever lol

Unpleasant staff members. Fries were exceptionally greasy, so I asked for my money back. They initially refused and kept asking why I didnt like them. I explained numerous times that the fries tasted stale and had the sitting-in-oil-too-long taste, which made them very unappetizing. A few more excuses later, the cashier finally returned my money. I normally enjoy NY fries...but not from this location.

This location is the most unhygienic one I came across specially in the evenings. The 2 guys sometimes touch the fries with their hands while packing. I asked for no green onions and while putting tomatoes on the fries, one green onion fell in my order, the guys noticed it and took it out using his hands, customer service and hygiene  should be a huge focus at this location!
Theres no cheese, no sour cream....just dry fires with onions thats what they call veggie fries, and with cherry on top no ketchup on counter...wow a great place to get fries but no ketchup
